explanation = '<MA>THE OLYMPIC GAMES</MA><TEXT>The only apparent theme answer, 17-across, tells us to PRESENT THE RINGS. There are exactly five O\'s in the puzzle, arranged like the Olympic rings. Additionally, both the across and down words of which each "ring" is a part are things that are the same colour as that particular ring. An ice FLOE and an OCEAN are blue like the upper-left ring, EBONY and OIL are black like the upper-middle ring, a ROSE and an ORANG are red like the upper-right ring, a LEMON and ODIE are yellow like the lower-left ring, and HOLLY and OKRA are green like the lower-right ring.</TEXT>'
